<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-792-111  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 792 111.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Dec 17 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Motorola Japan beefs up Japanese plant. (semiconductor plant inSendai, Japan)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Miyazawa, Masayuki.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Motorola Inc. (Planning).andO;Ticker:    MOT.andO;Topic:     Facility ConstructionManufacturingJapanMicroprocessorsHigh-Definition TelevisionNew Appointment.andO;Person:    Kuru, Isamu (Selection and appointment).andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>MOTOROLA JAPAN BEEFS UP JAPANESE PLANT 12/17/90 TOKYO, JAPAN, 1990 DEC 17(NB) -- President Rick Younts of Motorola Japan told the press that thecompany will build a plant to produce semiconductors.andP;  The plant will bebuilt in Sendai, northern Japan, at the cost of 80 billion yen ($6 billion).andM;At the new plant, Motorola is expected to produce the most advanced 32-bitchip as well as a chip for a high definition television (HDTV) jointly withToshiba.andP;  Motorola's relationship with Toshiba is already close enough --they have a chip-making joint venture dubbed &quot;Tohoku Semiconductor&quot; innorthern Japan.andM;Meanwhile, Motorola Japan has hired an ex-Toshiba man as its vice president.andO;President Younts has hinted that he will retire soon and Isamu Kuru isexpected to be replacing the current President around next April.andM;(Masayuki Miyazawa/121790/Press Contact: Motorola Japan, 03- 440-3311)</TEXT></DOC>